Class MatrixPopulation

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<MatrixModel>
          • gov.anl.cue.arcane.engine.matrix.MatrixPopulation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<MatrixModel>, java.util.Collection<MatrixModel>, java.util.List<MatrixModel>, java.util.RandomAccess

    public class MatrixPopulation
extends java.util.ArrayList<MatrixModel>
implements java.io.Serializable
    The MatrixPopulation class is a container for a sorted list of MatrixModels. The list is sorted in order of descending fitness value, with the highest value first (i.e., item zero) in the list.
